    {'Type': 'Tool', 'Name': 'Poison Flask', 'Weight': '0.15', 'BuyValue': '80 G', 'SellValue': '32 G', 'ForgeryCost': '120 G', 'Craftable': 'X', 'Combinableitem': 'X', 'Enhancingitem': '', 'img': 'resources/images/Poison Flask.png', 'desc': 'Poison Flask is an item available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "A flaskful of concentrated toxin. Hurl it at foes for it to work its poison." When held, it can be thrown at enemies, causing Thrown Damage, and may inflict Poison. When thrown at a poison resistant enemy it may inflict tarring instead. Obtained by filling an Empty Flask from a Poison pot. Such flasks are also sold at Camellia\'s Apothecary, and by the vendors Mathias, Delec, and Joye. They can also be stolen from\xa0Saurians\xa0using\xa0Master Thief.', 'ID': 93, 'id': 93},
