    {'ID': 1147, 'Name': "Vandal's Ring", 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': "resources/images/Vandal's Ring.png", 'desc': 'Vandal\'s Ring is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring imbued with a mysterious power. Wearing it boosts the power of projectile weapons such as Throwblasts." Obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3, and as a reward for the completion of the quest "An Unseen Rival II". The ring roughly doubles damage from throwing items. Two rings are even better. Thrown Damage', 'id': 1147},
    {'ID': 1148, 'Name': 'Bloody Knuckle', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Bloody Knuckle.png', 'desc': 'Bloody Knuckle is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring imbued with a mysterious power. Wearing it boosts the wearer\'s power when fighting barehanded." The Bloody Knuckle is a ring which doubles unarmed combat damage. It can be obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3, and is a reward for the Bitterblack Isle quest Slumbering Promise. Two rings quadruple damage. Bloody Knuckle continues to function for Unarmed Combat even if the secondary weapon (shield, bow) remai', 'id': 1148},
    {'ID': 1149, 'Name': 'Stonewall Earring', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Stonewall Earring.png', 'desc': 'Stonewall Earring is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring that boosts its wearer\'s Defenses, and their resistance to being knocked down or staggered while their mobility level is heavy or above." Boost Defense and Magick Defense by 40 and Stagger Resistance and Knockdown Resistance by 15% if encumbrance is heavy or above. Can be obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3, or as a reward for completing the quest, In Aid of the Emerald King III. The quest that rewards', 'id': 1149},
    {'ID': 1150, 'Name': 'Ring of Desiccation', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Ring of Desiccation.png', 'desc': 'Ring of Desiccation is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring imbued with a mysterious power. It encases its wearer in a waterproof membrane, putting an immediate end to the drenched debilitation." Can be obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3, or from one of the Moonbeam Gem treasure chambers in the Duskmoon Tower. The door is hidden at a mid level area that is reached by climbing a pillar and jumping into the room.\xa0 The ring does not completely prevent the weare', 'id': 1150},
    {'ID': 1151, 'Name': 'Ring of Perseverance', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Ring of Perseverance.png', 'desc': 'Ring of Perseverance is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring imbued with a mysterious power. \xa0It increases the discipline earned by the wearer." Discipline Points received by the wearer are increased by 50%, and wearing a second Ring of Perseverance will stack the effect. Can be obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3, or is guaranteed in a certain Moonbeam Gem treasure room in Duskmoon Tower - located on the east side of the first floor, behind the right hand do', 'id': 1151},
    {'ID': 1152, 'Name': 'Wanderlust Ring', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Wanderlust Ring.png', 'desc': 'Wanderlust Ring is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring imbued with a mysterious power. Increases the wearer\'s amount of Health restored when rescuing pawns." When unconscious pawns near death are aided they will gain three quarters of their full health if the Arisen is wearing this ring. Can be obtained by purifying Bitterblack Gear Lv.3. Stacks with the Restoration augment. Does not work in conjunction with the Mage staff Legion\'s Might.', 'id': 1152},
