    {'ID': 1156, 'Name': 'Savior Ring', 'Type': 'Jewelry', 'img': 'resources/images/Savior Ring.png', 'desc': 'Savior Ring is a jewelry piece available in Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen. "A ring that augments basic attributes." Obtained as a reward for the Quest Trappings of Evil. Boosts maximum Health by 500, and maximum Stamina by 500. Though it is not possible to get a second Ring from the above-mentioned Quest, it is possible to gift this Ring to rented Pawns, making it possible to have multiple Savior Rings.', 'id': 1156},
    {'ID': 1181, 'Name': "Set of Servant's Garb", 'Type': 'Female Outfits', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Servant's Garb.png", 'desc': 'Set of Servant\'s Garb is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "A set of clothing worn by servants in the castle. Meant for women, though men without shame might also wear it." Found only in the Duchess\'s Bedchamber from a gather spot behind a screen, but only at night. As of Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen the following changes have been made: Elemental Resistance: Burning +50% / Frozen +50% / Thundershock + 50% have been removed. Placative Brew May be found in chests, gather spots, breakables or just', 'id': 1181},
