    {'ID': 1183, 'Name': 'Set of Salvation Robes', 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': 'resources/images/Set of Salvation Robes.jpg', 'desc': 'Set of Salvation Robes is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "A set of black robes such as this signifies the wearer as an adherent to the cult of Salvation." A set can be found from a gather spot under the large cabinet in the Visitor\'s Chamber, within the Duke\'s Demesne, and in a chest in the second level underground in the Catacombs. Sets are also easily available through Mountebank at The Black Cat in Gran Soren. Rise of the Fallen. In this quest one way to proceed is to use a set of robes t', 'id': 1183},
    {'ID': 1184, 'Name': "Set of Fisherman's Garb", 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Fisherman's Garb.jpg", 'desc': 'Set of Fisherman\'s Garb is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "Traditional Cassardi wear, a hallmark of Gransys culture for generations." This is the clothing worn by the Arisen prior to the attack of the Dragon - their own set, damaged by the Dragon, become the unique Set of Fisherman\'s Tatters. Iola\'s shop will supply a new set in New Game Plus. As of Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen the following changes have been made: Elemental Resist: Frozen +20% has been removed. Debilitation Resist: Drenched', 'id': 1184},
    {'ID': 1185, 'Name': "Set of Fisherman's Tatters", 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Fisherman's Tatters.png", 'desc': 'Set of Fisherman\'s Tatters is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "Traditional Cassardi wear, a hallmark of Gransys culture for generations. The chest area has been rent apart." A damaged and bloodstained Set of Fisherman\'s Garb - this was the clothing worn by the Arisen during attack of the Dragon. As of Dragon\'s Dogma: Dark Arisen the following changes have been made: Debilitation Resistance: Drenched +30% has been removed. Hemp Sold by\xa0Iola\xa0at\xa0Iola\'s House\xa0in\xa0Cassardis. Sold by\xa0Reynard. Found', 'id': 1185},
    {'ID': 1186, 'Name': 'Set of Royal Guard Armor', 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': 'resources/images/Set of Royal Guard Armor.png', 'desc': 'Set of Royal Guard Armor is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "A replica of the armor worn by Gran Soren soldiers. Matches the look of the original, but cannot offer the same protection." This Soldier armor is only obtainable as a disguise given by Mirabelle at the start of the quest Duchess In Distress in order to infiltrate The Blighted Manse. The Royal Guard Armor Set allows the Arisen to enter The Blighted Manse by the front door, and also allows them to walk the Duke\'s Demesne at night wit', 'id': 1186},
    {'ID': 1187, 'Name': "Set of Lady's Garb", 'Type': 'Female Outfits', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Lady's Garb.jpg", 'desc': 'Set of Lady\'s Garb is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "The clothing of a fairly well-heeled lady. Meant for women, though men without shame might also wear it." Sold by Mountebank at The Black Cat in Gran Soren. White Orchid Found in a fairly wide range across the areas in the vicinity of Windbluff Tower, extending from the Deos Hills to the Northface Forest. Argence Found as random loot in chests in Soulflayer Canyon, The Blighted Manse, Bloodwater Beach, The Shadow Fort, The Tainted Mountai', 'id': 1187},
    {'ID': 1188, 'Name': "Set of Caretaker's Garb", 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Caretaker's Garb.png", 'desc': 'Set of Caretaker\'s Garb is DLC armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "Men\'s modest, high-quality attire. Gives an appearance of sincerity to whoever wears it." This is the outfit worn by Barnaby. Values in parentheses reflect changes in the Dark Arisen expansion. † Barrage and Draining attacks may have been intended to refer to the \'debilitations\' of Dark Critical Hit and Holy Healing - however this suit doesn\'t seem to protect against those effects. (It may refer to some other effect, or something', 'id': 1188},
    {'ID': 1189, 'Name': 'Forest Tunic Set', 'Type': 'Female Outfits', 'img': 'resources/images/Forest Tunic Set.jpg', 'desc': 'Forest Tunic Set is DLC armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "A woman\'s lightweight tunic made of soft, dark green silk. Its moisture-retaining properties make it a comfortable fit." This is the outfit worn by Selene. Values in parentheses reflect the Dark Arisen expansion. Reward for completing Speed Run mode. (Cannot be purchased anywhere) Can be gifted to a female pawn. Finest Herb Ale Brewed by\xa0Selene\xa0by giving her\xa0Sobering Wine. Perfect Herb Ale Obtained by combining\xa0Secret Herb Ale\xa0with\xa0Drop', 'id': 1189},
    {'ID': 1191, 'Name': "Set of Prisoner's Rags", 'Type': 'Outfits', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Prisoner's Rags.png", 'desc': 'Set of Prisoner\'s Rags is armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "Garb issued to castle prisoners when their equipment and possessions are confiscated." In Dragon\'s Dogma this clothing set had additional resistances\xa0: Thundershock +10% Tarring +25% The Arisen will automatically be equipped with this on being imprisoned in the Gran Soren Castle Dungeon. Shackle Dropped by a Bandit. Found at and in the near vicinity of The Ruins of Aernst Castle, on the roads just outside Gran Soren, the Wilted Forest', 'id': 1191},
    {'ID': 1192, 'Name': "Set of Jester's Motley", 'Type': 'Outfits', 'img': "resources/images/Set of Jester's Motley.jpg", 'desc': 'Set of Jester\'s Motley is DLC armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "The working uniform of the royal jester. Amusing in appearance, but comfortable and quite functional." A ridiculous red and gold outfit worn by Feste; the suit sports an extended integral cap with oversized bell, and a padded arse. The outfit has some elemental resistances, as well as excellent resistances to Sleep and Skill Stifling. In Dragon\'s Dogma - obtained from the DLC Armor Pack: Motley Crew. In Dark Arisen - can be bought', 'id': 1192},
    {'ID': 1193, 'Name': 'Nameless Armor Set', 'Type': 'Outfit', 'img': 'resources/images/Nameless Armor Set.jpg', 'desc': 'Nameless Armor Set is DLC armor available in Dragon\'s Dogma. "Shiny steel armor whose ponderous, looming design is something rarely seen in Gransys." Dark Arisen: Can be bought from The Black Cat. Dragon\'s Dogma: Obtainable from the A Face of a Different Color DLC, will be placed in Arisen\'s inventory, further copies can be bought from The Black Cat. Foreign Knife Sold by Madeleine at Madeleine\'s Shop in Gran Soren. Sold by Mathias at the Greatwall Encampment. May be gathered at Weapon/Armor Pil', 'id': 1193},
